iStock Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Nairobi - The United States has closed its embassy in Nairobi, Kenya for the day following a shooting on Thursday of a man who had stabbed a policeman outside the embassy building, BBC says.The embassy released a statement to its citizens regarding the incident and its operational hours."Review your personal security plans, remain aware of your surroundings, including local events, and monitor local news stations for updates. Be vigilant and take appropriate steps to enhance your personal security," a statement from the embassy read.The man who was killed has been identified as a Kenyan Somali from Wajir.Confirmed: Shooting incident near the Embassy. No Embassy personnel were involved. We refer you 2 Kenyan authorities 4 further details.We will be closed on Friday, October 28. Please see the Security Message for U.S. Citizens here: https://t.co/IYOfZgufVuReports indicated earlier that the dead man had been walking towards the US embassy and was close to the public entrance to the visa section when he attempted to grab a gun from one of the officers. A photograph shared on social media showed the body of the lying on the pavement, a pool of blood staining the tarmac by his head, and surrounded by police officers. US Federal Bureau of Investigation (FBI) officers were also present at the scene. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.